white and cor\ndovan. Special, pair,\n25c\n4\nMen\u2019s and Boys\n9\nN F urnishing Specials\nUnderwear\nMen\u2019s Wool Shirts and Draw\ners; Special, garment\u2014\n$1.35\nMen\u2019s Two-piece Underwear,\nribbed and flat fleeced; garment\n75c\nMen\u2019s Ribbed Union Suits,\ncream or grey; Special, suit\u2014\n$1.00\nMen\u2019s Wool Union Suits; Spe\ncial, suit\u2014\n$2.95\nGowns\nI Men\u2019s Flannelette Gowns; Spe\nI cial\u2014\n$1.00\nOveralls\nBest quality Blue-stripe Overalls\nand Jumpers; Special, garment\n$1.35\nHose\nMen\u2019s heather mixed Wool Hose;\nSpecial, pair\u2014\n50c\nI Men\u2019s Wool Hose; dark, light\ngrey and black; pair\u2014\nt\nI\n25c\n\nq\nGloves\nMen\u2019s leather palm Canvas\nGloves, gauntlet style; pair\u2014\n25c\nI\nShirts\nMen\u2019s Blue Jersey Overshirts;\nSpecial\u2014\n$1.00\nI\nPants\nBoys\u2019 Corduroy Pants, pair\u2014\n$1.\n[ill]\n\nShirts\nBoys\u2019 Cheviot Shirts, collar at\n1 tached\u2014\n75c\nPants\nYouths\u2019 Khaki Pants, size 27 to\n31; Special, pair\u2014\n$1.\nAYA\u2019\n010\n1\nTT\nOveralls\nYouths\u2019 plain blue or striped\nOveralls; sizes 27 to 31; pair\u2014\nI\n$1.00\nMadden Says Cost\nof Carrying Mail in\nPlane is Excessive\n(Continued from Page 8)\nMadden said that.the last train that\nleaves New York' City at night for\nChicago leaves at 8:40 p. m. The\npresumption is that that train takes\nall the mail available up to 8:40\no\u2019clock. The airmail service would,\ntherefore, take mail deposited in the\n\u2014ere-A di \u2014=e \u2014od UUPM-UU m mo\npostoffice after 8:40 p. m. and leave\nfor Chicago with it the next morn\ning.\nThe airplane, however, does\nnot carry the mail clear through to\nChicago, but takes it to Cleveland\nand transfers it to the train, taking\non other mall from the Cleveland\ntrain, which mail is carried to Chi\ncago.\nThere the mall is left and\nother mail taken on, going to some\nother point farther west, and this\nprocess is repeated at fixed inter\nvals.\nMr. Madden asserted that while\nthe letters are expedited in trar\nversing a part of the route, yet in\nthe end there is no actual saving of\ntime.\nThe airplane from Chicago\nleaves at 7 o'clock in the morning\nand arrives in New York about 6\no\u2019clock in the evening. The letters\nwould not be delivered the same\nnight, and since they must lie over\nnight in the New York postoffice and\nbe delivered sometime the following\nday, there is practically no saving\nof time. Mr. Madden intimated that\nthere is also considerable loss of\ntime due to the fact that the flying\nfields are often many miles from\npostoffices. He believed that in some\ninstances a letter would be actually\ndelayed rather than expedited by\ntransportation by the air route.\nThe Postoffice Department has dis\ncontinued the use of airplane postage\nstamps and the airplane mail is made\nup of letters carrying two cents an\nounce postage* deposited in the regu\nlar mails.\nFewer Passengers\non Street Cars\nThe general business depression\napparent in practically every indus\ntry is being reflected in street rail\nway travel, D. EL Parsons, general\nmanager of the East St Louis\nSuburban Railway Co., said this\nmorning\n\"Figures on travel for the second\nweek of January show a decline of\nbetween 13 per cent and 16 per cent\nas compared with corresponding\nweeks of October, November and\nDecember,\u201d said Parsons. \"Approxi\nmately 60,000 passengers less were\ncarried on cars of the Bolleville divi\nsion last month than in December\nof 1919.\u201d\nThe decrease tn revenue is noted\nparticularly on the State street.\nEighteenth street and Broadway divi\nsions of the railway company, it\nwas stated. Falling off in travel on\nthe Broadway line can be traced to\nthe cutting down of the forces at the\nAluminum Ore Company and Amer\nican Steel Foundries, it is stated.\nBave The Dairy Journal Visit Your\nHome Every Day.\nDON\u2019T SUFFER\nWITH NEURALGIA\nUse Soothing Musterole\nWhen those sharp pains go shooting\n